hands_on_practices.solution:
We seek the zero-sound dispersion in 2D with only $F_{0}^s\neq0$.  Defining $s\equiv c_0/v_F$, the Landau kinetic equation yields the eigenvalue condition
$$1 - F_0^s\int_0^{2\pi}\frac{d\phi}{2\pi}\,\frac{\cos\phi}{\,s-\cos\phi\,}=0\,. $$

1.  Evaluate the angular integral:
$$I(s)=\int_0^{2\pi}\frac{d\phi}{2\pi}\,\frac{\cos\phi}{s-\cos\phi}
=\frac{s}{\sqrt{s^2-1}}-1\,,\qquad s1\,. $$

2.  Substitute into the dispersion equation:
$$1 - F_0^s\biggl(\frac{s}{\sqrt{s^2-1}}-1\biggr)=0
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad F_0^s\frac{s}{\sqrt{s^2-1}}=1+F_0^s\,. $$

3.  Rearranging,
$$\frac{s}{\sqrt{s^2-1}}=\frac{1+F_0^s}{F_0^s}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad\frac{\sqrt{s^2-1}}{s}=\frac{F_0^s}{1+F_0^s}\,. $$

4.  Square both sides:
$$1-\frac1{s^2}=\frac{(F_0^s)^2}{(1+F_0^s)^2}
\;\Longrightarrow\;\frac1{s^2}
=1-\frac{(F_0^s)^2}{(1+F_0^s)^2}
=\frac{2F_0^s+1}{(1+F_0^s)^2}\,. $$

5.  Hence
$$s^2=\frac{(1+F_0^s)^2}{\,1+2F_0^s\,}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad c_0
=v_F\,\frac{1+F_0^s}{\sqrt{1+2F_0^s}}\,. $$
